text: General elections were held in Liechtenstein on 8 February 2009. While polls and pundits predicted few changes, the Christian democratic Patriotic Union (VU) gained an outright majority in the Landtag, whilst the national conservative Progressive Citizens' Party (FBP) and the green social democratic Free List (FL) both suffered losses. ==Results== {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:right" ! colspan="2" |Party !Votes !% !Seats !+/– |- | bgcolor="" | | align="left" |Patriotic Union |95,219 |47.6 |13 | +3 |- | bgcolor="" | | align="left" |Progressive Citizens' Party |86,951 |43.5 |11 |–1 |- | bgcolor="" | | align="left" |Free List |17,835 |8.9 |1 |–2 |- | colspan="2" align="left" |Total |200,005 |100 |25 |0 |- ! colspan="6" | |- | colspan="2" align="left" |Valid ballots |15,124 |– | colspan="2" rowspan="4" | |- | colspan="2" align="left" |Invalid/blank ballots |1,052 |– |- | colspan="2" align="left" |Total ballots cast |15,650 |100 |- | colspan="2" align="left" |Registered voters/turnout |18,493 |84.6 |- | colspan="6" align="left" |Source: Landtagswahlen |} === By electoral district === {| class="wikitable" !Electoral district !Seats !Electorate ! colspan="2" |Party !Candidates !Votes !% !Swing !Seats won !+/– |- | rowspan="3" |Oberland | rowspan="3" |15 | rowspan="3" |12,105 | bgcolor="" | |Patriotic Union | |71,469 |48.9 | 9.9 |8 | 2 |- | bgcolor="" | |Progressive Citizens' Party | |61,033 |41.7 | 5.0 |6 | 1 |- | bgcolor="" | |Free List | |13,733 |9.4 | 4.9 |1 | 1 |- ! colspan="11" | |- | rowspan="3" |Unterland | rowspan="3" |10 | rowspan="3" |6,388 | bgcolor="" | |Patriotic Union | |23,750 |44.2 | 8.0 |5 | 1 |- | bgcolor="" | |Progressive Citizens' Party | |25,915 |54.3 | 6.1 |5 |0 |- | bgcolor="" | |Free List | |4,102 |7.6 | 1.9 |0 | 1 |- ! colspan="11" | |- | colspan="11" |Source: Landtagswahlen |} ==References== Category:2009 elections in Europe 2009 parliamentary Category:2009 in Liechtenstein Category:February 2009 events in Europe
